protocol.name: P-G5524-1
protocol.text: For cold acclimation plants were transferred to a growth room at 4Â°C with a 9/15 hour day/night cycle. Material was harvested after 11 days of growth at hour 5 of the light cycle (cold acclimated control). At the end of the light cycle plants were frozen at 6.0Â°C for 20 hours, then placed at 20Â°C in the dark for 3 hours, at which time a sample was collected. Plants were left in the dark at 20Â°C for a total of 24 hours at which time a second sample was collected.
